My name is Lauren and I am the General Manager of WVBR 93.5-FM. I have been in Cornell Media Guild since 2020, working on the Music and Programming side of operations. Radio has been my most treasured college experience and now, I am so excited for a successful year in CMG as your GM.I am a senior in the Arts & Sciences College Scholar Program, studying Cognitive Science and Multimedia with a minor in Information Science. Outside of WVBR, I enjoy collecting vinyl records, playing video games, watching/listening to/analyzing film and music, and playing bass in my local band Skip Tracer. I look forward to another amazing year in Cornell Media Guild, and I hope to utilize radio to emphasize and reinforce the incredible musical community we have here in Ithaca while further cultivating our growing student community.If you have any questions or concerns for me, please feel free to contact me personally at gm@wvbr.com or lgt28@cornell.edu. Thank you! Greg Kerr Hi! I’m Greg Kerr and I am a junior at Cornell studying History. I am the Treasurer for WVBR. I handle all the finances for the organization, monitoring all transactions coming in and out. I execute payroll, pay taxes, balance the books, talk to the bank, and more! It isn’t much on the surface but I do my best to keep things running behind the scenes. Outside of WVBR I am involved with the Museum Club here on campus and EBR (our recording studio in the same building as WVBR). Catch me taking a break from doing work whenever I can. Emily Choi I am a senior Communication major in CALS, minoring in business and art. Given my new position as Corporate Secretary, I am excited to be involved in the various subsidiaries and serve the Guild as best I can. I enjoy marketing, writing, and painting and recently got super into golfing! I joined CMG towards the end of the spring semester due to Kate Snow’s Cornell visit; She talked about how what she learned in WVBR continues to play a pivotal part in her career. I hope this organization can be a hub where we create more big and small moments of inspiration for members and those who have yet to join the Guild! Dean Reiter \u200b Chase Miller Hi, my name is Chase and I am the president of Electric Buffalo Records. I have been part of EBR since my first semester at Cornell and am now responsible for overseeing all of EBR’s operations including signing artists, running our recording studio, and planning events. I’m excited to continue bringing together music lovers across Cornell to build this great community.Outside of EBR, I am a senior in Dyson concentrating in business analytics and entrepreneurship. I enjoy doing music production for hip hop and r&b artists as well as spending time outdoors. Faith Shote My name is Faith Shote, and I am in the College of Arts and Sciences majoring in Biological Sciences with a concentration in Genetics and minoring in Law & Society. I’m so excited to step into the roles of Program and Sports Director at WVBR to revitalize the station! I love music and sports, which makes my jobs at WVBR very fun! A few of my favorite genres of music are pop, indie, alternative, reggaeton, and country! I love listening to new music so please send me your music recommendations. The sports leagues I keep up with are Cornell sports, of course, NFL, college football, MLB, NHL, Premiere League soccer, and my personal favorite Formula 1 racing.Tune in to Big Red Banter every Saturday from 4-5pm or stream on all podcasting platforms to hear me and the WVBR sports department chat about all things sports! Do not hesitate to reach out to discuss anything WVBR and/or music and sports!! Carla Escanillas \u200b Abby Schulman Hi! I’m Abby and I am a junior in Arts & Sciences pursuing an independent major within the College Scholar Program. Since joining CMG as a freshman, I have primarily worked in Sales & Business. In my first role as Business Director, I reported to the Sales Manager and GM, brainstorming strategies to increase revenue for the Guild. I have been Sales Manager for the Guild since fall 2021. In my position, I communicate with local and national advertisers on a regular basis, and have closed numerous significant deals. CMG has provided me with hands-on business experience, as well as a community of great people who are passionate about music and the media industry. Outside of CMG, you can find me singing a cappella with The Key Elements, as well as playing guitar, reading, and listening to music. I am looking forward to another great year at the station! Rachel Korosi \u200b Hannah Devine-Rader \u200b Joanna Teran Hi! I am a sophomore aiming to major in Communication. I joined CMG in the fall semester of my freshman year as a part of the Marketing and Promotions team. In the spring, I wanted to become more involved with the organization, and ran to become the Alumni Relations Director. I’m excited to act as a liaison between the Guild’s current members and its alumni and come up with events for us to connect. In my spare time, I can be found watching sitcoms or reading celebrity memoirs. Maeve Lathrop Henry Hylbert \u200b Ivan Kwong \u200b Andrew Modrowsky \u200b Jack Donnellan I am a second-year undergraduate student at Cornell University interested in law, public policy, and education hailing from Brooklyn, New York. I joined the WVBR news department in the fall of my first semester, and have been here ever since! As Co-News Director, I co-produce and host "Talk of The Town," our innovative, flagship talk news show, assigning and editing stories written by the reporting team. I also oversee the daily operation of the news department, including the publication of a podcast, written news and editorial content. In addition to my role at WVBR, I’m involved in various organizations on campus, including Cornell Ambassadors for Media & Performance (CAMP) and College Mentors for Kids. If you’ve got any questions, or have a scoop you’d like to share with me, feel free to reach out via email at news@wvbr.com. Anjali Kumar I am a sophomore at Cornell studying Communication with an intended minor in Fashion Design Management. I am WVBR’s Content Manager, so I create graphics, ads, and social media materials for the station as part of the Marketing and Promotions Team. I love WVBR because of the variety of alternative music we play on our station that’s perfect for chill late-night study sessions, morning drives, and strolls around Cornell’s beautiful campus. Outside of WVBR, you can find me singing in my co-ed a cappella group, The Key Elements, or meticulously curating Spotify playlists for every aesthetic. Noah Braun Hi! My name is Noah, and I manage the content of the website you\'re looking at right now! I\'m a junior studying computer science and information science, and avid indie music listener and vinyl collector. Other than my role at WVBR, I\'m an active member of several other campus organizations, such as being the director of promotions for the Cornell Concert Commission, the vice president of the Development in Games Association, and the Treasurer for the Magic: The Gathering club. Will Swartzentuber \u200b Ally Knapp \u200b Lily Josephson \u200b \u200b WVBR is a local commercial radio station broadcasting from Ithaca, New York to the Counties of Tompkins, Tioga, Cortland, Cayuga, Seneca, Schuyler, and Chemung. WVBR is run by the Cornell Media Guild, Inc - a non-profit student organization that is independent and not funded nor managed by Cornell University. Our mission is to preserve local media and act as a training ground for the future generation. All views represented by our contributors solely reflect their own views, and are not necessarily endorsed by WVBR or Cornell Media Guild. \u200b Cornell Media Guild is a registered student organization of Cornell University. \u200b © Cornell Media Guild, Inc. All Rights Reserved. \u200b 604 E Buffalo St. Ithaca, NY 14850 (607) 273-4000 info@wvbr.com \u200b \u200b Designed by Michelle Davies (2022). \u200b \u200b'}]
